OL,7,F"We are dealing with a situation where
OL,8,Fa person, in different circumstances,
OL,9,Fis allowed to go into rooms without
OL,10,Finvitation. That is quite a unique
OL,11,Fsituation. This is a person who is
OL,12,Fentitled to go into a room and search
OL,13,Fwardrobes.
OL,15,F"It may well have been the case that
OL,16,Fhe went into the room for other
OL,17,Freasons and, while in the room, he
OL,18,Fcommitted this theft, and therefore
OL,19,Fthe burglary. It is a very different
OL,20,Fsituation from someone who is kicking
OL,21,Fdown a door and forcing entry.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/14
